<TEXT>
<P>
European Community foreign ministers agreed to send emergency food aid to 
Poland pending a wider international effort to tackle structural problems of 
food supply there. The 12 ministers were responding to the decision at the 
Paris summit by the seven leading industrialized democracies to ask the 
European Community to coordinate help for economic reforms in Poland and 
Hungary. A preparatory meeting of officials of the 12 community governments 
will be held soon to prepare a conference to examine ways to help Polish 
agriculture overcome problems causing chronic shortages. 
</P>
