<HEADLINE>
<P>
MITCHELL KOS KELLY AT FORUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Russell Mitchell won the North American Boxing Federation welterweight 
championship Monday by knocking out former champion Derrick Kelly of Riverside 
in the seventh round of their scheduled 12-round bout at the Forum. 
</P>
<P>
Mitchell, of Quail Valley, Calif., was rated No. 10 by the NABF. He was 
outpointed in the first five rounds as Kelly took command. 
</P>
<P>
Mitchell responded with a short right cross that struck Kelly on the temple and 
at 2:52 of the seventh round, referee Chuck Hassett counted Kelly out. 
</P>
<P>
Kelly is 24-2-2 with nine knockouts and Mitchell is 16-10-3, also with nine 
knockouts. 
</P>
<P>
In an earlier bout, Kenny Baysmore of Washington knocked out Benny Lopez of 
Upland in the first round of their scheduled 10-round quarterfinal Forum super 
featherweight tournament match. 
</P>
<P>
Baysmore knocked Lopez down with a right, and referee Lou Moret ended the bout 
at 2:59 of the first round. 
</P>
<P>
Baysmore is 25-2-1, with 21 knockouts, and Lopez is 13-6, with nine knockouts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
