</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HOUSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bystanders did nothing to help two toddlers who had fallen into a swimming 
pool, said an emergency official who was able to save one of the children. 
</P>
<P>
Fire Capt. C. A. Beasley pulled the two girls from the pool Sunday, but one of 
them, 15-month-old Tiffidie Anne McGough, was dead. Her 2-year-old half-sister, 
Taffidie, was in critical condition Monday in Texas Children's Hospital. Their 
mother was asleep in a nearby apartment when the girls fell into the water. 
</P>
<P>
Beasley told the Houston Chronicle that two men were standing by the apartment 
house pool when he arrived, and they told him there were "dolls or dogs" in the 
water. 
</P>
<P>
"Regardless of what they thought they were, I can't imagine anybody standing 
there looking at two kids in the pool," Beasley said. 
</P>
