<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
La Habra-based Landmark Bancorp and its subsidiary, Landmark Bank, reported 
consolidated second-quarter earnings of $498,000, an 85% increase from the 
$269,000 posted for the like period last year. Deposits rose 9%, to $145 
million from $133 million. The bank's asset base rose 10%, to $160 million from 
$146 million. For the first six months of the year, net income increased 60%, 
to $932,000 from $582,000 for the first half of 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
