<P>
GREEKS DROP PAPANDREOU'S LAWYER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ATHENS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Greek government gave the New York lawyer of defeated Socialist Prime 
Minister Andreas Papandreou a $200,000 "golden handshake" today and dropped him 
from the state payroll. 
</P>
<P>
Lawyer Leonard Boudin was handling Papandreou's libel suit against Time 
magazine and was in charge of efforts to extradite fugitive Greek banking 
tycoon George Koskotas, who is jailed pending extradition hearings in the 
United States. 
</P>
<P>
Boudin filed charges against Time in Britain last April, saying the weekly news 
magazine libeled Papandreou in carrying an extensive interview with Koskotas. 
Koskotas accused the Papandreou government of approving a plan to pocket 
millions of dollars in interest payments from state accounts at the private 
Bank of Crete, which he controlled until fleeing in November. 
