<P>
WILLIAMS TO DROP CHARGES IN DIVORCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BATON ROUGE, La. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Washington Redskins quarterback Doug Williams has agreed to drop a forgery and 
theft complaint against his estranged wife, an attorney for Lisa Williams said 
today. As part of a divorce agreement, Lisa Williams will also have custody of 
the couple's child, said attorney Lewis Unglesby. 
</P>
<P>
The settlement is to be finalized after being signed by the judge, Unglesby 
said. 
</P>
